The funeral service for award-winning gospel musician Dennis Mwangi, alias Papa Dennis, was conducted at the Nairobi Chapel on Ngong' Road on Monday. The 'Nashukuru' hitmaker's body was discovered by the roadside in Pangani, Nairobi, on the night of February 7, an accident which shocked many in the showbiz industry and fans. The funeral service was attended by politicians, celebrities, families and friends, who showered praises on the fallen star. Among those present were his twin brother Simon Mwangi, his former manager Sadat Muhindi, Starehe MP Charles 'Jaguar' Kanyi and Saboti MP Caleb Amisi. The send-off service was organised by gospel singer Alex 'Ringtone' Apoko.